---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { AUTHOR } from '../consts';
import brianPhoto from '../assets/images/brian.jpg';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title="About"
      description="Background, work, and how I think about engineering."
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <div class="header">
        <div class="header-text">
          <h1>How I think about engineering.</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            I build and operate production systems for organisations where
            reliability is non-negotiable — banks, healthcare AI platforms,
            energy. My work sits where deep technical engineering meets the
            outcomes it enables: uptime, regulatory confidence, customer trust.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="header-photo">
          <Image
            src={brianPhoto}
            alt="Brian Muli Muteti"
            width={220}
            height={220}
            loading="eager"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Current</h2>
      <p>
        I am currently at <strong>KCB Bank</strong> in Nairobi, working on
        DevOps and Site Reliability Engineering across core banking
        platforms.
      </p>

      <h2>Background</h2>
      <p>
        Before KCB I led Site Reliability Engineering for Africa at
        <strong>Qure.ai</strong>, an AI-driven healthcare diagnostics platform with
        multi-country deployments. Before that I was a DevOps and SRE
        engineer at a Tier-1 East African bank, where I built much of
        the work documented in <a href="/work">case studies</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        I hold a BSc in Electrical and Electronics Engineering from the
        Technical University of Mombasa, and I am a registered Graduate
        Engineer with the Engineering Board of Kenya.
      </p>

      <h2>How I work</h2>
      <p>
        I treat reliability as a business outcome, not a technical
        metric. The systems I build are observable, fault-tolerant,
        and designed for the engineers who operate them — not just the
        ones who built them. I lead with documentation, runbooks, and
        post-incident learning. I mentor.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside of full-time engineering, I serve as Head of Operations
        for the Association of Energy Professionals in Eastern Africa.
      </p>

      <h2>Certifications</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>AWS Certified DevOps Engineer — Professional (DOP-C02)</li>
        <li>AWS Certified Solutions Architect — Associate (SAA-C03)</li>
        <li>
          AWS Cloud Quest badges: Generative AI Architect, Solutions
          Architect, Cloud Practitioner, Amazon Connect Fundamentals
        </li>
        <li>Google Data Analytics Professional Certificate</li>
        <li>Google Project Management Professional Certificate</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        The best way to reach me is by <a href={`mailto:${AUTHOR.email}`}>email</a>.
        I am also on <a href={AUTHOR.linkedin}>LinkedIn</a> and write on
        <a href={AUTHOR.medium}>Medium</a>.
      </p>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .header {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    gap: var(--space-8);
    align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }
  .header-text { min-width: 0; }
  .header-photo :global(img) {
    width: 180px;
    height: 180px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    object-fit: cover;
    filter: grayscale(0.1);
    display: block;
  }
  .lede {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .header {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-6);
    }
    .header-photo {
      order: -1;
    }
    .header-photo :global(img) {
      width: 140px;
      height: 140px;
    }
  }
</style>